doc.after: The 767 has been produced in three fuselage lengths.[24] These debuted in progressively larger form as the 767-200, 767-300, and 767-400ER, respectively.[24][115] Longer-range variants include the 767-200ER and 767-300ER,[115] while cargo models include the 767-300F, a production freighter,[116] and conversions of passenger 767-200 and 767-300 models.[117]
